The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Murali to miss next Test too
                                                   Murali to miss next Test too
                      
	Colombo: Sri Lanka spinner Muttiah Muralidharan is still having treatment on a knee injury and will miss the second Test against Pakistan starting Sunday. He also missed the first Test.         
	The 37-year-old, who has injured his patella tendon, is doubtful for the third Test.         
	Wicket-keeper Prasanna Jayawardene returned to full training this week, but was also not considered for selection as Sri Lanka, who lead the three-match series 1-0 named an unchanged squad.         
	The only selection dilemma is the form of opener Malinda Warnapura.         
	Sri Lanka captain Kumar Sangakkara called for improvement from his batsmen.           (REUTERS)                                                                                                                   
